title: PreSonus Studio One 3 Reference Manual v1.0.0.9-R2R
description:
PreSonus Studio One 3 Reference Manual v1.0.0.9 for StudioOne-R2R [deepstatus]

This is the Studio One Operation Manual. Contained within this document are the details of the "nuts and bolts" of the software which will be key to your learning to understand and operate this Professional digital audio workstation (DAW).

Alternatively, you can also access your Studio One manual from Studio One's start page by pressing the F1 key on your keyboard on both Mac and PC computers. Note: For this option to work as stated above, you must have Adobe Reader or another .PDF reader installed.

Furthermore, you can search the manual by hitting the Control + F on Windows and Command + F on MAC and entering a phrase or keyword to search the manual.

* An important note: Studio One's reference manual is written for the Professional version of StudioOne. If you are running the Artist or Producer version, please see the break down chart that explains what options are included in your version of StudioOne if you find a discrepancy in the verbiage in the manual and what you see in your version of StudioOne.

1) Open Studio One
2) Click the "Help" menu
3) In the drop down click "Studio One Reference Manual"

Earlier Versions of Studio One:

1) Open Studio One
2) Click the "Help" menu
3) In the drop down click "Contents"

You will need to have Adobe Reader or another .PDF reader installed
